          <name xml:lang="en">carbon content, fossil</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">dimensionless</unitName>
          <comment xml:lang="en">Cast iron is made by remelting pig iron in small furnaces (e.g. cupola furnaces or electric arc furnaces) and poured into moulds to make castings. It usually contains 2% to 6% carbon (ecoinvent v2.2 report 10_partII). An average content of 4% was considered</comment>
